Title: Design a simple Neural network model

Source code:
#Aim: Design a simple neural network model	
w = float(input("Enter the value of weight:"))
b = float(input("Enter the value of bias:"))
x = float(input("Enter the value of input:"))

#Calculate with formule Yin=b+Wx
print("The net input(Yin):")
Yin = float(b+w*x)
print(Yin)

: Calculate the output of neural net
Source code of problem statement A

Source code:
#Aim: Calculate the output of neural the input X=[x1,x2,x3]=[0.3,0.5,0.6] and weight   w=[w1,w2,w3]=[0.2,0.1,-0.3]

n = int(input("Enter the number of input Neurons:"))
# W will take weight and X will take the input
w = []
x = []

for i in range (0,n):
    a =  float(input("Enter the input:"))
    x.append(a)
    b = float(input("Enter the weight:"))
    w.append(b)
    print("The given weight are:")
    print(w)
    print("The given input are:")
    print(x)
    y = 0.0
    for j in range(0,n):
        y = y+(w[i]*x[i])
        print("The net input is:")
        print(round(y,3))
        
        
